President Donald Trump has issued a proclamation honoring the men and women who serve in the United States military on Armed Forces Day. He praises their dedication and valor in preserving the nation's peace and defending its founding principles. The President emphasizes the importance of supporting and taking care of the Armed Forces, highlighting the recent gains against ISIS and al-Qa'ida in Syria and Iraq. He also mentions the signing of legislation providing funding for national defense and a pay raise for troops. President Trump calls upon all Americans to display the U.S. flag and learn more about military service on Armed Forces Day.